title: One dead, six wounded in house-party shooting
content:
The six wounded guests were taken to area hospitals with what appeared to be non-life-threatening injuries.
Deputies believe the violence erupted from a dispute over a woman, said Jane Watrel, a sheriff's spokeswoman. Multiple guns were involved. Neighbors told the Orlando Sentinel they heard dozens of gunshots before ambulance and law enforcement officers began arriving about 5 a.m.
Almost two years ago, a birthday party ended in gunfire about 2:30 a.m. at the same location.
Two people were wounded in that incident, one who was found on the lawn and another who drove himself to Health Central Hospital in Ocoee before deputies arrived about. That incident and the latest one are not related, Watrel said.
Investigators want anyone who witnessed the shootings or anyone who knows the identity of the woman to call Crimeline at 800-423-8477.
